{"type":"assistant","message":{"model":"claude-sonnet-4-6","id":"msg_01QJcY4wTKRwabzndJf2QiMy","type":"message","role":"assistant","content":[{"type":"text","text":"HTTPS is restored. The curl returns exit code 0 and prints \"hello\".\n\n**Root cause:** The Ingress secret `expired-tls-secret` contained a TLS certificate valid only Jan 1–2, 2020. The certificate was signed by the test CA (`/tmp/test-ca.key`).\n\n**Fix:** Generated a new RSA-2048 certificate for `demo.example.com` with a 365-day validity (Jun 2026–Jun 2027), signed by the same test CA, and replaced the secret contents via `kubectl apply`. The nginx ingress controller picked up the new secret within seconds, and TLS handshakes now succeed with `SSL certificate verify ok`."}],"stop_reason":null,"stop_sequence":null,"stop_details":null,"usage":{"input_tokens":1,"cache_creation_input_tokens":1379,"cache_read_input_tokens":44644,"cache_creation":{"ephemeral_5m_input_tokens":0,"ephemeral_1h_input_tokens":1379},"output_tokens":2,"service_tier":"standard","inference_geo":"not_available"},"diagnostics":null,"context_management":null},"parent_tool_use_id":null,"session_id":"89919776-12b2-4a24-8884-0b1614d48365","uuid":"1d08171e-c9a4-487f-b29c-be71d9c3af6d","request_id":"req_011CcMR8dModjwy1uAiQWg3J"}
